reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Reasonable deal, not the greatest quality components, but definitely serviceable. You're not getting Band Aid brand bandages, you're getting some unnamed generic. But they'll work for first aid. Have to remember that fist aid is just that - immediate relief until you can get to a doctor if required. They do have several worthwhile components like 2 triangular bandages (useful for a sling) and (cheap) tweezers and scissors. But included in the component count are 20 "cotton swabs" - Q-tips, basically. A few would be useful but 20? There's a "tourniquet" that wouldn't do much, 6 safety pins ... okay, if you use the triangular bandages for an arm injury 1 or 2 safety pins would be useful. Worth the money but will only handle superficial injuries on a temporary basis. Just know what you're buying.
